race.comment: A few key runners come out which opens this up for SWITCH HIT (3). Found a good track for only the second time in his career recently and was far too good over this distance at Bendigo. Finds a similar race today and can repeat the dose. SHEER LUNACY (1) did a great job to score under 61kgs last Monday. Won here over this distance at the only attempt. After the claim looks well placed to run another big race. SAINT LOFT (7) has lost his way a bit since a tough first-up win at the Wagga Riverside. Back in trip last start which wasn't ideal. On a seven-day back-up and goes well at the mile so can bounce back. KEITH (4) is fitter for two runs back from a spell. Has raced nine times over this distance for a couple of wins and five minor placings. Sure to give a good account. WINNING WITNESS (10) gets a couple of key gear changes and is in the mix on a seven-day turnaround.
